
# PSDE - Configure Cross-Tenant Access Settings In Microsoft Entra
#### [Made by Joanna Zibbell with Scribe](https://scribehow.com/o/3rgKI9W4TF-GdZqMRM28tA/viewer/PSDE_-_Configure_Cross-Tenant_Access_Settings_In_Microsoft_Entra__JmKO_w-PQCmT0Uv3rL6k3A)
How to configure cross-tenant synchronization between an agency tenant and the PSDE Workforce tenant so agency-managed users and groups can automatically receive access to shared Microsoft Fabric resources.

Tip: Cross-tenant synchronization is not required to for PSDE participation. Up to 10 users, agencies can use manual B2B onboarding.


#### Target & Source Tenant: Set Up Cross-tenant access settings


Tip: Both the source and the target tenants need to complete this section.

WFCA = Target Tenant

PSDE Agency = Source Tenant


1\. Navigate to [https://entra.microsoft.com/](https://entra.microsoft.com/?utm_source=chatgpt.com#view/Microsoft_AAD_IAM/GroupsManagementMenuBlade/~/Overview/menuId/Overview)

![](https://colony-recorder.s3.amazonaws.com/files/2026-05-26/79b11e62-303d-42bd-aa6f-3a59d024dd4e/ascreenshot_45c09fda75ca47ba8212df1a15aa38e3_text_export.jpeg)


2\. Click "External Identities" then "Cross-tenant access settings"

![](https://colony-recorder.s3.amazonaws.com/files/2026-05-29/24d040af-4f5f-4a77-a803-dc018ecace63/user_cropped_screenshot_0b4c5ae3d44c4b39b2836aab59feedd9_text_export.jpeg)


3\. Click "Add organization"

![](https://colony-recorder.s3.amazonaws.com/files/2026-05-27/b690d3df-942c-42df-86d5-1999082d4488/ascreenshot_bf18baef4867479bbb4c7b4983f1e463_text_export.jpeg)


4\. PSDE Agency search for[wfca.com](https://wfca.com) and WFCA search for agency domain such as [ocfa.org](https://ocfa.org)Confirm the results and press Add.

![](https://colony-recorder.s3.amazonaws.com/files/2026-05-26/00ca3f3b-2b8d-4b48-a6ad-6a14ae527278/ascreenshot_cac7ec97f6044496ba3544e295bbee2a_text_export.jpeg)


5\. For Source Tenants in a GCC tenant, WFCA is in a commercial tenant so both entities need to configure "Microsoft cloud settings" to allow collaboration. The GCC tenant will check "Microsoft Azure Commercial"

![](https://colony-recorder.s3.amazonaws.com/files/2026-05-29/f44ef538-21a3-409c-a06f-9a8f6e57cc51/user_cropped_screenshot_87c25fea2f8748ceba82896e3f6bdda0_text_export.jpeg)


#### Target Tenant: Configure Inbound Access Settings for PSDE Agency Cross Tenant Organization


Tip: Only the target tenant (WFCA) configures Inbound Access settings.


6\. Click "Inherited from default" under Inbound access for the added organization.

![](https://colony-recorder.s3.amazonaws.com/files/2026-05-29/c3255402-19cf-4e51-9125-5f328e012479/user_cropped_screenshot_96eca114b19141a2a9f420351debf76d_text_export.jpeg)


